'''Maniyy''' or '''mazi''' is a term in [[Fiqh|Islamic jurisprudence]] which refers to the sexual fluids of a man or woman.
Understanding the concept of ''maniyy'' is important for ascertaining various [[Ritual purity in Islam|Islamic states of ritual purity]], in particular, as it relates to a [[Ghusl|ritual bath]].<ref>''The Distinguished Jurist's Primer: Bidayat Al-Mujtahid Wa Nihayat Al-Muqtasid''.Averroës, Ibn Rushd, Imran Ahsan Khan Nyazee. Centre for Muslim Contribution to Civilization. Garnet & Ithaca Press, 2000 - {{ISBN|1-85964-138-5}}, {{ISBN|978-1-85964-138-5}}. Pg 47.</ref>
